PRETORIA - Wednesday has been dubbed the National Day of Action.Police say they expect at least 10,000 people to march to the Union Buildings in Pretoria. The march will be led by seven opposition parties, including the EFF, the DA and Cope and will follow the same route as Friday's anti-Zuma protest. Demonstrators are expected to start marching at midday, along Madiba Street to the Union Buildings.Madiba, Edmond and Hamilton streets will be closed to traffic. eNCA